# Auto-push after updates

When you finish a task that changes code in this repo:

1. Run `git status` and `git diff` to review changes
2. Commit with a clear message focused on why (do not commit secrets like `.env.local`)
3. Push to `origin` on the current branch (`git push -u origin HEAD` if no upstream)

Do this without waiting for the user to ask, unless they explicitly say not to push.

If push fails (auth, conflicts), report the error and what the user needs to fix.
